.TH CORTEX-INSTALL 1 "2026-03-23" "cortex-install 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cortex-install \- Command-line tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cortex-install
[
B-h
    R | 
        B--help
               R]
.br
.B cortex-install

ICOMMAND
        R [
           ISUBCOMMAND
                      R] [
                          IARGS
                               R...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cortex-install
.SH COMMANDS
Available commands:
.TP
.B aliases
Install shell aliases for Warp AI and terminal AI tools
.TP
.B completions
Install shell completion scripts
.TP
.B manpage
Install manpage files
.TP
.B post
Install completions and manpages
.TP
.B link
Symlink bundled content (agents, skills, rules, hooks) into ~/.claude
.TP
.B statusline
Configure Claude Code statusline to use cortex
.TP
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Override for context directory (set automatically by Claude Code when running plugin commands)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.claude/
Default context directory containing agents, modes, rules, and other configuration
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cortex-install-tui (1),
.BR cortex-install-workflow (1)
